page.title: 05WIS. GREEN CUB SCOUTS
page.content: The cubs' and scouts' hutis situated in Harsfold Lane off the A272 going out of Wisborough Green towards Billingshurst.The Akela runs the cubs which starts at six o'clock and finishes at seven-thirty.There are about twenty cubs in the pack. A favourite game is "Port and Starboard" which is where all the cubs line up and Akela shouts some commands like "Port", "Starboard" or "Lifeboats" and the cubs run to the appropriate side of the room. Their uniform is a green jumper, a green and white scarf and a green peaked cap. The cubs have two camps like the scouts.They are the Petworth Park camp and summer camp.
